      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "[codex] add native macOS fleet VNC viewer",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Add a native macOS 14 SwiftUI/AppKit control deck for Crabfleet and generic VNC servers.\n- Provide a searchable fleet grid, saved profiles, quick connect, matched card-to-desktop transitions, full-screen focus, and a desktop switcher.\n- Keep up to six sessions warm with focused, background, and inactive frame pacing plus bounded cached previews.\n- Render IOSurface-backed frames with Metal through a locally modified RoyalVNCKit fork.\n- Keep the viewer deployment-neutral; no provider-specific deployment integration is included.\n\n## Product behavior\n\n- Supports RFB 3.3, 3.7, and 3.8 with no-auth and VNC-password authentication.\n- Includes app-owned, opt-in clipboard synchronization: focus gating, stable pasteboard snapshots, delayed-echo suppression, background quarantine, explicit Send/Get actions, and clear propagation.\n- Accepts manual VNC endpoints and can read the public Crabfleet fleet API; broker/CLI contracts for one-click connection setup remain follow-up work.\n- Pins the CryptoSwift dependency revision and records third-party notices and fork provenance.\n\n## Security and licensing\n\n- Raw VNC transport is unencrypted. Production connections should use an authenticated SSH loopback tunnel.\n- The modified RoyalVNCKit D3DES source has ambiguous provenance. Replace or remove it, or obtain explicit licensing approval, before distributing the app.\n- Clipboard synchronization is disabled by default and currently supports standard ISO-8859-1 text only; Unicode extended clipboard, images, and files are not included.\n\n## Validation\n\n- `pnpm macos:test`: 38 passing tests (20 RoyalVNCKit, 18 app).\n- RoyalVNCKit suite passes under Thread Sanitizer.\n- Strict-concurrency diagnostic build succeeds; remaining warnings are in vendored Swift 6 migration paths.\n- Live loopback coverage: RFB 3.3 no-auth, RFB 3.3 VNC-password, full 720×450 frame delivery, and simultaneous focused/background pacing.\n- Optimized ad-hoc app bundle builds, signs, and passes strict code-signature verification.\n- Visual smoke test passed; idle sample showed 0.0% CPU and about 56 MB physical footprint.\n- Independent clipboard/security review and structured code review found no remaining P1/P2 issues.\n- Public-diff audit found no provider-specific code, internal hosts, local paths, or credentials.\n\n## Follow-ups before distribution\n\n- Resolve the D3DES licensing gate.\n- Add the authenticated Crabfleet connection broker and SSH tunnel lifecycle.\n- Move from paced cached fleet previews to a zero-copy Metal mosaic compositor if profiling justifies it.\n- Add a production Xcode target, hardened runtime, Developer ID signing, and notarization.",
